BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Wizard of Oz
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260717T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260717T220000
DTSTAMP:20260718T091704Z
UID:occ-1421@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:The 1939 MGM songbook onstage\, Toto played by a puppet\, from
  Walton County's community theatre.\n\nThe stage adaptation of the 1939 MG
 M film\, with the Harold Arlen and E. Y. Harburg songs intact\, 'Over the 
 Rainbow' included. A Kansas farm girl is swept into Oz and heads down the 
 yellow brick road with a scarecrow\, a tin man\, and a cowardly lion\, hop
 ing the Wizard can send her home. In this production Toto is a puppet in t
 he Lion King mold\, and the Munchkins are played mostly by children. Marc 
 Hammes directs for On Stage Playhouse\, Walton County's community theatre\
 ; runs through July 26.
GEO:33.7934843;-83.7059787
LAST-MODIFIED:20260717T203557Z
LOCATION:On Stage Playhouse\, 215 High School Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.tickettailor.com/events/onstageinc/2277613
END:VEVENT
